Klasse PersonFilter

java.lang.Object
de.fherfurt.librarySystem.logic.PersonFilter
public class PersonFilter extends Object
The PersonFilter class defines filter criteria for searching people in a library system based on borrowed books, outstanding fees, and the number of borrowed books.

    • PersonFilter

      public PersonFilter(List<Book> books, double minOpenFees, double maxOpenFees, int minBooksBorrowed, int maxBooksBorrowed)
      Constructor for creating a PersonFilter object with specified criteria for borrowed books, minimum and maximum outstanding fees, and the minimum and maximum number of borrowed books.
      Parameter:
      books - the list of books to filter by
      minOpenFees - the minimum outstanding fees to filter by
      maxOpenFees - the maximum outstanding fees to filter by
      minBooksBorrowed - the minimum number of borrowed books to filter by
      maxBooksBorrowed - the maximum number of borrowed books to filter by
